# load dataset for all meta-analyses 
# Place the data set in the same folder with the .Rmd file to load data or specify the Github path

dat_sleep <- read.csv("sleep.csv")
dat_depress <- read.csv("depression.csv")
dat_anxiety <- read.csv("anxiety.csv")

1.1 Subjective sleep outcome meta-analysis

m.sleep <- metacont(n.e=n.e,
                    mean.e=mean.e,
                    sd.e=sd.e,
                    n.c=n.c,
                    sd.c=sd.c,
                    mean.c=mean.c,
                    studlab=Author,
                    data=dat_sleep,
                    sm="SMD",
                    method.smd="Hedges",  
                    fixed=FALSE,
                    random=TRUE,
                    method.tau="REML",  
                    hakn=TRUE, # for small sample size 
                    title="Music intervention on Sleep Quality")
summary(m.sleep)
## Review:     Music intervention on Sleep Quality
## 
##                             SMD             95%-CI %W(random)
## Blanaru et al, 2012     -0.6533 [-1.4456;  0.1391]       14.2
## Hernandez-Ruiz, 2005    -0.2888 [-1.0341;  0.4564]       14.3
## Lu et al, 2022          -4.1038 [-4.9854; -3.2223]       13.9
## Lund et al, 2022        -0.6695 [-1.0595; -0.2796]       15.2
## Niet et al, 2010        -0.2463 [-1.0394;  0.5469]       14.2
## Jespersen & Vuust, 2012 -0.2102 [-1.2469;  0.8264]       13.4
## Yang et al, 2021        -1.5154 [-2.0938; -0.9370]       14.8
## 
## Number of studies combined: k = 7
## Number of observations: o = 325
## 
##                          SMD            95%-CI     t p-value
## Random effects model -1.0940 [-2.3735; 0.1855] -2.09  0.0814
## 
## Quantifying heterogeneity:
##  tau^2 = 1.7189 [0.6184; 9.3066]; tau = 1.3111 [0.7864; 3.0507]
##  I^2 = 90.5% [83.0%; 94.7%]; H = 3.25 [2.43; 4.35]
## 
## Test of heterogeneity:
##      Q d.f.  p-value
##  63.32    6 < 0.0001
## 
## Details on meta-analytical method:
## - Inverse variance method
## - Restricted maximum-likelihood estimator for tau^2
## - Q-Profile method for confidence interval of tau^2 and tau
## - Hartung-Knapp (HK) adjustment for random effects model (df = 6)
## - Hedges' g (bias corrected standardised mean difference; using exact formulae)
# Sleep forest plot 
forest.meta(m.sleep, 
            sortvar = TE,
            prediction = FALSE, 
            print.tau2 = FALSE,
            leftlabs = c("Author", "g", "SE"),
            label.right = "Favors control",
            label.left = "Favors intenvention")

# sleep funnel plot 

col.contour = c("gray75", "gray85", "gray95")  # color
funnel.meta(m.sleep, xlim = c(-5, 2),
            contour = c(0.9, 0.95, 0.99),
            col.contour = col.contour,
            studlab=FALSE)
legend(x = .8, y = 0.01, 
       legend = c("p < 0.1", "p < 0.05", "p < 0.01"),
       fill = col.contour)
title("Sleep Quality")

# Sleep Outlier tests (Lu 2022)
m.sleep.inf <- InfluenceAnalysis(m.sleep, random=TRUE)
## [===========================================================================] DONE
plot(m.sleep.inf, "influence")

1.2 Subjective sleep outcome meta-analysis without outlier (Lu 2022)

# Delete outlier: Lu 2022
s1.dat_sleep <- dat_sleep[dat_sleep$Author != "Lu et al, 2022",]

# re-run the meta analysis (Sleep S1) 
s1.sleep <- metacont(n.e=n.e,
                    mean.e=mean.e,
                    sd.e=sd.e,
                    n.c=n.c,
                    sd.c=sd.c,
                    mean.c=mean.c,
                    studlab=Author,
                    data=s1.dat_sleep,
                    sm="SMD",
                    method.smd="Hedges",
                    fixed=FALSE,
                    random=TRUE,
                    method.tau="REML",
                    hakn=TRUE,
                    title="Music intervention on Sleep (S1)")
summary(s1.sleep)

3.1 Anxiety meta-analysis

# remove one measure for Blanaru et al (removed STAI from Blanaru et al) due to the double measures 
dat_anxiety <- dat_anxiety %>% filter(mean.e!=65.7)
m.anxiety <- metacont(n.e=n.e,
                    mean.e=mean.e,
                    sd.e=sd.e,
                    n.c=n.c,
                    sd.c=sd.c,
                    mean.c=mean.c,
                    studlab=Author,
                    data=dat_anxiety,
                    sm="SMD",
                    method.smd="Hedges",
                    fixed=FALSE,
                    random=TRUE,
                    method.tau="REML",
                    hakn=TRUE,
                    title="Music intervention on Anxiety")
summary(m.anxiety)
